    },
    {
        "describing the behavior of soil. Soil Behavior and Critical State Soil Mechanics, Wood, David Muir, Cambridge University Press, 1990.      ": null
    },
    {
        "Geotechnical centrifuge modeling": "Geotechnical Centrifuge Modeling"
    },
    {
        " is a method of testing physical scale models of geotechnical problems. The use of a centrifuge enhances the similarity of the scale model tests involving soil because the strength and stiffness of soil is very sensitive to the confining pressure. The centrifugal acceleration allows a researcher to obtain large stresses in small physical models.       Geotechnical engineers are typically graduates of a four-year civil engineering program and some hold a ": null
    },
    {
        "masters degree": "Masters Degree"
